# XML Documentation

Summaries for public classes and interfaces must not be empty.

- If a documentation comment exists, the `<summary>` tag must contain meaningful text.
- Both single-line (`/// <summary>Description.</summary>`) and multi-line format are allowed.
- Do not leave `/// <summary></summary>` or `/// <summary>   </summary>` with no or only whitespace content.

```csharp
// BAD
/// <summary></summary>
public class Foo { }

/// <summary>
/// </summary>
public interface IBar { }

// GOOD
/// <summary>Application configuration (domain model).</summary>
public class AppSettings { }

/// <summary>
/// Renders one visualization mode from an analysis snapshot.
/// </summary>
public interface IVisualizer { }
```
